T1	Intervention 174 606	To evaluate the effect of metformin on insulin sensitivity and to further examine the relationship between insulin resistance, sympathetic nerve activity and blood pressure, 6 obese insulin resistant, normoglycemic hypertensive men were investigated (age 49 +/- 2 years, BMI 27.6 +/- 1.2, mean +/- SEM). The study had a placebo controlled, double blind, cross over design with 6 weeks' metformin treatment (850 mg b.i.d) vs placebo.
